";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:362:\"Introduction WPTouch is a popular WordPress plugin that allows you to display your site’s content on mobile devices. It can send mobile-optimized content, pictures, scripts, and CSS code instead of ‘normal’ ones. This speeds things up considerably. It also allows your iOS visitors to save your website like an app. WPTouch works great with WPML. [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Mohamed Khafaja\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10084:\"<h3><span style=\"color: #4a8aa7\"><strong>Introduction</strong></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wptouch.com/\"><em>WPTouch</em></a> is a popular WordPress plugin that allows you to display your site’s content on mobile devices. It can send mobile-optimized content, pictures, scripts, and CSS code instead of ‘normal’ ones. This speeds things up considerably. It also allows your iOS visitors to save your website like an app.</p>\n<p><em>WPTouch</em> works great with WPML. In this tutorial, we will explain how to translate text that comes with <em>WPTouch</em> themes and extensions.</p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #4a8aa7\"><strong>What You Will Need:</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A recent version of <a href=\"https://wpml.org/purchase/\">WPML</a>, including the String Translation and Translation Management add-ons</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"http://www.wptouch.com/pricing/\"><em>WPTouch</em> plugin</a></li>\n<li>One of <em>WPtouch</em>’s extensions (We use the <a href=\"http://www.wptouch.com/themes/\">Mobilestore theme</a> in this tutorial)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #4a8aa7\"><strong>Essential Resources:</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>WPML’s <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/\">Getting Started Guide</a> will help you in setting up WPML in only a few minutes. You will want to refer to some of its subtopics later, such as <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/theme-localization/\">Theme and Plugin Localization</a> and <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/getting-started-guide/string-translation/\">String Translation</a>. We recommend you keep the Getting Started Guide open while following this tutorial.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.wptouch.com/support/home\">WP Touch documentation</a> has an excellent collection of tutorials that can help you get started.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #4a8aa7\"><strong>Translating </strong><strong>Strings Coming from WPTouch Themes and Extensions</strong></span></h3>\n<p><em>WPTouch</em> allows one-click downloading and installation of additional themes and extensions. The extensions are saved in <em>wp-content/wptouch-data</em>. As you can see, this path is outside the default plugin directory. <em>WPML String Translation scans </em> everything inside the themes directory (<em>wp-content/themes</em>) and the plugins directory (<em>wp-content/plugins</em>). We will create and import .po files into the String Translation table so you can translate these strings with WPML.</p>\n<p>First, make sure you enabled theme and plugins localization in WPML, You can do that by going to WPML &gt; Theme and plugin localization, then choosing “Translate the theme and plugins using WPML’s String Translation.”</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-811197 \" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image1.png\" alt=\"Translate the theme and plugins using WPML’s String Translation\" width=\"601\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image1-300x137.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/image1.png 752w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 601px) 100vw, 601px\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Mobilestore theme, which is a <em>WPTouch</em> extension, does not come with a .po file, so we must create one.</p>\n<p>Obtain zipped theme files from your site after it is downloaded using the <em>WPTouch</em> installer. This can be done by following these steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to the WordPress directory.</li>\n<li>Then, go to wp-content/wptouch-data/themes.</li>\n<li>Locate the theme folder. In our case, it will be the “mobilestore&#8221; folder.</li>\n<li>Download the mobilestore files and compress them with a .zip extension.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-811219\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file1-300x271.png\" alt=\"create .po file1\" width=\"372\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file1-300x271.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file1.png 763w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 372px) 100vw, 372px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The second step is to create our .po file:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>After getting the zipped theme file, you can extract strings and export .po files using various tools. <em>ICL PHP Scanner</em> will do the trick. <a href=\"http://www.icanlocalize.com/tools/php_scanner\">http://www.icanlocalize.com/tools/php_scanner</a></li>\n<li>Upload the zipped file by clicking on the “Browse…” button next to “PHP file to process (required)”:.</li>\n<li>Click on the ”Create .po file &gt;&gt;” button. This creates the <em>wptouch-pro.po </em></li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file2.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-811226\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file2-300x199.png\" alt=\"create .po file2\" width=\"436\" height=\"289\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file2-300x199.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file2-768x510.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/create-.po-file2.png 915w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 436px) 100vw, 436px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Once you have the <em>wptouch-pro.po</em> file, upload it to your site using the WPML String Translation screen. Remember to assign the correct context for imported strings (if the  <em>wptouch-pro</em> context is missing, create a new context with that name).</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WPML &gt;&gt; String Translation &gt;&gt; Import / export .po section.</li>\n<li>Next to “.po file”:, click the ”Browse…” button and upload the <em>wptouch-pro.po</em></li>\n<li>Choose “Also create translations according to the .po file.”</li>\n<li>Choose the string domain from the drop down menu next to “Select what the strings are for:” <strong>Note that </strong>you can create a new domain by clicking on “new” then typing the domain name (wptouch-pro).</li>\n<li>Click on the “Submit” button</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-.po-file-to-string-translation.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-811229\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-.po-file-to-string-translation-300x151.png\" alt=\"add .po file to string translation\" width=\"485\" height=\"244\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-.po-file-to-string-translation-300x151.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-.po-file-to-string-translation-768x386.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-.po-file-to-string-translation-1024x515.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-.po-file-to-string-translation.png 1213w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 485px) 100vw, 485px\" /></a></p>\n<p>After the upload is finished, you will be redirected to the string selection screen. Select all the strings you want to translate, then click on “Add selected strings.”</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-selected-strings.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-811231\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-selected-strings-300x137.png\" alt=\"add selected strings\" width=\"495\" height=\"226\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-selected-strings-300x137.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-selected-strings-768x351.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-selected-strings-1024x468.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/add-selected-strings.png 1065w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 495px) 100vw, 495px\" /></a></p>\n<p>After importing the strings, registered strings which are ready to be translated can be found on the <em>WPML &gt;&gt; String Translation</em> screen. <strong>Note that </strong>you can find all the strings under the wptouch-pro domain.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-811240\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-300x156.png\" alt=\"string translation\" width=\"486\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-150x78.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-300x156.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-768x400.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation-1024x534.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/string-translation.png 1076w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 486px) 100vw, 486px\" /></a></p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #4a8aa7\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></span></h3>\n<p>Creating .po files and importing them into WPML String Translation tables will register the strings to be translated on the string translation screen. This can only be done when the installed plugin, theme or extension has its own directory (not under the default directory).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=3Z_s_Ma1KmA:GHDwIJS8Muk:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=3Z_s_Ma1KmA:GHDwIJS8Muk:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=3Z_s_Ma1KmA:GHDwIJS8Muk:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=3Z_s_Ma1KmA:GHDwIJS8Muk:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=3Z_s_Ma1KmA:GHDwIJS8Muk:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=3Z_s_Ma1KmA:GHDwIJS8Muk:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/3Z_s_Ma1KmA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://wpml.org/2016/02/how-to-translate-a-string-coming-from-wptouch-themes-and-extensions/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://wpml.org/2016/02/how-to-translate-a-string-coming-from-wptouch-themes-and-extensions/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"What our users say about the WooCommerce Multilingual plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/haWC_lCznZ8/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"https://wpml.org/2016/02/what-our-users-say-about-the-woocommerce-multilingual-plugin/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 11 Feb 2016 12:17:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Case studies\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"https://wpml.org/?p=810198\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:361:\"The WooCommerce Multilingual plugin allows you to turn your WooCommerce store into a multilingual one. That’s the theory. How does it look like in practice? Is this process easy or difficult? Will translating your products into foreign languages help your business to grow? We asked these questions to our WPML customers who built their multilingual [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Agnes Bury\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19353:\"<p>The <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/related-projects/woocommerce-multilingual/\">WooCommerce Multilingual plugin</a> allows you to turn your WooCommerce store into a multilingual one. That’s the theory. How does it look like in practice? Is this process easy or difficult? Will translating your products into foreign languages help your business to grow?</p>\n<p>We asked these questions to our WPML customers who built their multilingual online stores with WPML plugins. See what they answered.</p>\n<h2>Authors and multilingual stores they built</h2>\n<table class=\"table table-bordered\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_810320\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-810320\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-810320\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1-300x212.png\" alt=\"wundersocks.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"212\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1-150x106.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1-300x212.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1-768x544.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1-1024x725.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-strore-1.png 1243w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">wundersocks.com</p></div></td>\n<td><strong>Site:</strong> <a href=\"http://wundersocks.com\">wundersocks.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong><br />\nOnline store selling wool socks, special socks, designed by Sport Mayrl, a family-owned business.</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> German, English, Italian</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Lukas Mairl, CEO of wundersocks.com</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_810321\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-2.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-810211\"><img class=\"wp-image-810321 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-2-300x225.png\" alt=\"www.littleandpure.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-2-300x225.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-2-768x576.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-2-1024x768.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-2.png 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">www.littleandpure.com</p></div></td>\n<td><strong>Site:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.littleandpure.com/\">www.littleandpure.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong><br />\nOnline store selling custom designed children’s beds and accessories. It’s targeted towards mothers and mothers-to-be.</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> English, German, Dutch</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Boris Hoekmeijer &#8211; a designer/developer, self-employed, the owner of <a href=\"http://borishoekmeijer.nl\">borishoekmeijer.nl</a>. He made this site for his customer, a mother of four kids.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_810322\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-4.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-810218\"><img class=\"wp-image-810322 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-4-300x225.png\" alt=\"gpstrackshop.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-4-300x225.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-4-768x576.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-4-1024x768.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-4.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">gpstrackshop.com</p></div></td>\n<td><strong>Site:</strong> <a href=\"http://gpstrackshop.com\">gpstrackshop.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong><br />\nA web store for people with interest in tracking their vehicle, children, valuables or pets with GPS trackers.</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> English, German</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Daniël Brito, the CTO of GPSTrackShop.com</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_810325\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-3.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-810219\"><img class=\"wp-image-810325 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-3-300x225.png\" alt=\"www.blackeyeusa.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-3-300x225.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-3-768x576.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-3-1024x768.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-3.png 1279w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">www.blackeyeusa.com</p></div></td>\n<td><strong>Site</strong>: <a href=\"http://www.blackeyeusa.com/\">www.blackeyeusa.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Description:</strong><br />\nBlackeye is the manufacturer of camera pods for action filming without the need for special cameras. Their pods are niche products and need a broad, international audience.</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> English, German</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Stefan Wiesmeth, General Manager of Blackeye</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>4 reasons for making stores multilingual with WPML</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-810222\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/reasons-for-making-stores-multilingual-with-WPML.jpg\" alt=\"4 reasons for making stores multilingual with WPML\" width=\"500\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/reasons-for-making-stores-multilingual-with-WPML-300x181.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/reasons-for-making-stores-multilingual-with-WPML-768x463.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/reasons-for-making-stores-multilingual-with-WPML.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p>First, we asked our interviewees why they decided to build an online store and why they chose the WPML plugins. Here are their reasons:</p>\n<h3>#1 &#8211; Reaching broader audience</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“We wanted to reach as many customers as possible. Having a multilingual website is a must. Most of our customers are based in Italy, Austria, Switzerland and Germany. That&#8217;s why we chose to go with Italian, German and English as our main three languages.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Lukas Mairl</em></p>\n<h3>#2 &#8211; Not everybody knows English, even if you think they do</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“We launched GPSTrackShop.com in English only and noticed a lot of Dutch visitors were having difficulties with the website because of that. This is when we thought that we should translate the website. But knowing that it would cost a lot of time to make a copy of the website we searched for a solution and found WPML as the best solution.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Daniël Brito</em></p>\n<h3>#3 &#8211; because of WooCommerce itself</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“I used WooCommerce as, in my experience, it is the best webshop solution for WordPress.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Boris Hoekmeijer</em></p>\n<h3>#4 &#8211; make you customers comfortable while shopping</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“We wanted our customers to feel confident during the shopping process. WPML works very well and is stable &#8211; and that’s essential we think. The price of the WPML plugin is very reasonable and absolutely affordable &#8211; especially for small businesses and start-ups.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Stefan Wiesmeth</em></p>\n<h2>Was it easy or difficult?</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-810261\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-easy-or-difficult.jpg\" alt=\"multilingual store - easy or difficult\" width=\"500\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-easy-or-difficult-300x181.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-easy-or-difficult-768x463.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-easy-or-difficult.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p>Creating an online store is a challenge itself. Making it multilingual is like raising your game to another level. Was the process easy or difficult for our customers?</p>\n<h3>Easy</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“It was easy to setup the WPML plugin, but I had to find out where to do the translations of more complex features like custom fields and plugins. After reading the manual and trying, I found the way to do so. So on a scale of 1 to 10 (not difficult – very difficult) I would say a 2.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Daniël Brito</em></p>\n<h3>Quite a bit of work</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“Making WPML and WooCommerce work properly was quite a bit of work, actually. Setting it all up took a lot of time, and after that, we experienced a couple of issues, some related to WooCommerce Multilingual plugin (bugs that seem to have been fixed) as well as other plugins (WooCommerce/Yoast SEO plugin).</p>\n<p>I am very careful now of updating any of the WooCommerce related plugins, as my confidence in the system has been dented somewhat. Stability over time will hopefully erase my doubts. “</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Boris Hoekmeijer</em></p>\n<h3>Fairly easy</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“It was fairly easy to setup the plugin. After reading the documentation and playing with different settings we were able to get the site out pretty fast.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Lukas Mairl</em></p>\n<h3>We, as non-programmers, needed some time</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“We have no programming skills, but we made it work well. Our goal was to use our WordPress theme, WooCommerce and WPML together, without the help of a programmer and without customizing any code. Obviously we needed some time to learn how everything works and what’s possible, but we made it.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Stefan Wiesmeth</em></p>\n<h2>How it affected their business</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-810277\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-pays-off.jpg\" alt=\"How multilingual store affected their business\" width=\"500\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-pays-off-300x181.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-pays-off-768x463.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/multilingual-store-pays-off.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p>Ok, so it takes a while to put it all together and make your store multilingual. Did it pay off?</p>\n<h3>From a small showcase site to getting real profits</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“I designed and built the website, I don’t own the business. My client does, and it has definitely helped her. At first, the website was mainly a showcase for her self-designed products to attract re-sellers, now she can actually sell them herself to consumers. That has given her profits a nice boost!”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Boris Hoekmeijer</em></p>\n<h3>Simply said: Best investment we made.</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“The biggest effect is the fact that our content has now better SEO results. Because if a person searches in Google for our products with Dutch terms, they will find our product is now much higher than before.</p>\n<p>For example If we compare the month before and after the launch of the WPML plugin: 200% more income, 80% more visitors, 15% decrease of bounce rate, 10% increase in average pageviews per user and I can keep on going about all the improvements. Simply said: Best investment we made.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Daniël Brito</em></p>\n<h3>Customers from all over the word</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“It affected our business a lot. After setting up the multilingual site we were able to reach even more people around the world. We are now receiving many orders for example from the USA, Canada and UK. “</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Lukas Mairl</em></p>\n<h3>We set it up ourselves and saved a lot of money</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“Our online shop definitely needs to be multilingual for our business. Using WordPress and the WPML plugin saves us a lot of cost for programmers and maintenance. We can now do it all by ourselves. “</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Stefan Wiesmeth</em></p>\n<h2>What they liked the most about the plugin</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-810284\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/best-of-WooCommerce-multilingual.jpg\" alt=\"What they liked the most about the plugin\" width=\"500\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/best-of-WooCommerce-multilingual-300x181.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/best-of-WooCommerce-multilingual-768x463.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/best-of-WooCommerce-multilingual.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p>The WPML core and the WooCommerce Multilingual plugin are rich in a wide range of different features. What did our customers like the most?</p>\n<h3>Simple setup and useful settings</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“We like the simple setup. Also it provides a lot of useful settings. Our goal was to get the site out as fast as possible. Coding something from scratch would have taken up too much time and too many resources.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Lukas Mairl</p>\n<h3>User language auto detection</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“There are a couple of things I like about the plugin, but one of my favourites is the fact that the plugin comes with a building feature to show the correct language according to the user local language.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Daniël Brito</p>\n<h3>The bridge between WPML and WooCommerce</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“The WooCommerce Multilingual plugin bridges that gap between WPML and WooCommerce, which is exactly what I was looking for. What I don’t really understand though, is that translating products works so differently from regular posts. It would have made sense to me to have it set up like that.”</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Boris Hoekmeijer</p>\n<h3>Stability and excellent support</h3>\n<blockquote><p>“It integrates well and doesn’t create trouble. Only once we had a minor issue, caused by a WordPress update; however, it got resolved with a new WPML update a few days later. Can absolutely recommend WPML!“</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Stefan Wiesmeth</p>\n<h3>Conclusion and upcoming improvements to multilingual WooCommerce</h3>\n<p>WPML team is aware that WooCommerce Multilingual has room for improvement. At this very time, we are completing a major update to WooCommerce Multilingual. <strong>This update addresses a number of usability problems which we have already identified.</strong></p>\n<p>The configuration is getting a reorganization uplift, so that it will simpler to set up the multilingual options of e-commerce sites.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_810297\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/products.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-810297\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-810297\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/products-1024x379.png\" alt=\"Changes coming in the new release\" width=\"1024\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/products-300x111.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/products-768x284.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/products-1024x379.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Changes coming in the new release</p></div>\n<p>The biggest boost in this version is in the <strong>new product translation editor</strong>. We are changing everything in the current editor, making it easier to find products that require translation and to translate them.</p>\n<p>Translation will also be possible for both site admins and the ‘translators’ of the site.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_811121\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-810299\"><img class=\"wp-image-811121 size-large\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new-1024x715.png\" alt=\"Translation will also be possible for both site admins and the ‘translators’ of the site.\" width=\"1024\" height=\"715\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new-150x105.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new-300x209.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new-768x536.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new-1024x715.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/translate-product-new.png 1046w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Translation will also be possible for both site admins and the ‘translators’ of the site.</p></div>\n<p>We are planning a first beta release in about two weeks and a production release shortly after.</p>\n<h2>What is your experience?</h2>\n<p>How about you? Have you ever built an online store with WordPress? Maybe you have some plans but also some doubts. What are they? <strong>Please share your experience with us.</strong></p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=haWC_lCznZ8:pvLH-PEzanA:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=haWC_lCznZ8:pvLH-PEzanA:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=haWC_lCznZ8:pvLH-PEzanA:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=haWC_lCznZ8:pvLH-PEzanA:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=haWC_lCznZ8:pvLH-PEzanA:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=haWC_lCznZ8:pvLH-PEzanA:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/haWC_lCznZ8\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://wpml.org/2016/02/what-our-users-say-about-the-woocommerce-multilingual-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://wpml.org/2016/02/what-our-users-say-about-the-woocommerce-multilingual-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"WPML 3.3.6 – Maintenance Release\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/5lW3kBYztPA/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/wpml-3-3-6-maintenance-release/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 27 Jan 2016 12:29:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"WPML versions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"https://wpml.org/?p=797281\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:343:\"We updated WPML to version 3.3.6 today. This release includes a number of improvements and fixes. Nothing major or dramatic and no new features. It&#8217;s good to run the most recent release for best stability and performance. Fixed browser redirect, so redirect only happens if the current page language is not one of the preferred [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amir\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2986:\"<p><strong>We updated WPML to version 3.3.6 today. This release includes a number of improvements and fixes. Nothing major or dramatic and no new features. It&#8217;s good to run the most recent release for best stability and performance.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed browser redirect, so redirect only happens if the current page language is not one of the preferred browser languages</li>\n<li>Fixed different results produced in non default languages by queries with mixed post type and taxonomies in filter</li>\n<li>Improved Translation Management notice handling in core</li>\n<li>Fixed issue with post status when post date sync is enabled</li>\n<li>Fixed issue in Yoast SEO sitemap which was not showing taxonomies in other languages than default</li>\n<li>Added compatibility with Gravity Forms <a href=\"http://www.gravityforms.com/add-ons/quiz/\">Quiz add-on</a></li>\n<li>General performance improvements</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Download and update</h2>\n<p>You should receive this update automatically to your WordPress admin, for all the sites where you registered WPML. You can also download manually from your <a href=\"https://wpml.org/account/\">WPML.org account</a>, under <strong>Downloads</strong>.</p>\n<h2>What next?</h2>\n<p>This is a minor maintenance release, but WPML team is working on a much more significant update for you. WPML 3.4, which is getting ready for first beta, will include a completely new Translation Editor, Translation Jobs Queue and support for translating taxonomy terms meta. We hope to have a solid beta version of it early next week.</p>\n<p>BTW, while we&#8217;re on the subject of translation taxonomy terms, you might be interested to learn that our <a href=\"https://wp-types.com\">Types plugin</a> is getting support for taxonomy meta too. You can use <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/2016/01/types-1-9-beta1/\">Types beta</a> and see how taxonomy meta works on your development sites.</p>\n<h2>Feedback?</h2>\n<p>We love getting your feedback. Leave us your comments with questions, ideas and suggestions. If you are asking about a technical issue, first, report it in our <a href=\"https://wpml.org/forums/forum/english-support/\">technical support forum</a>. You&#8217;re also welcome to leave here a comment with a link to your thread, so I can follow up.</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=5lW3kBYztPA:9JeQIRe7QH8:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=5lW3kBYztPA:9JeQIRe7QH8:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=5lW3kBYztPA:9JeQIRe7QH8:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=5lW3kBYztPA:9JeQIRe7QH8:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=5lW3kBYztPA:9JeQIRe7QH8:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=5lW3kBYztPA:9JeQIRe7QH8:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/5lW3kBYztPA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/wpml-3-3-6-maintenance-release/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"8\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/wpml-3-3-6-maintenance-release/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"Five rules you should know before building WordPress real estate sites\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/E7E9z2HGOpU/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/five-rules-you-should-know-before-building-wordpress-real-estate-sites/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 22 Jan 2016 08:50:46 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Case studies\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"https://wpml.org/?p=790460\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:369:\"At first glance, they all look similar: tons of pictures with properties, a handy search, and maps. Today’s real estate websites are responsive and attractive. Some convert visitors into clients better than others, but what exactly makes a real estate website successful? We interviewed three WordPress developers from different parts of the world who built [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Agnes Bury\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33229:\"<p>At first glance, they all look similar: tons of pictures with properties, a handy search, and maps. Today’s real estate websites are responsive and attractive. Some convert visitors into clients better than others, but what exactly makes a real estate website successful?</p>\n<p>We interviewed three WordPress developers from different parts of the world who built successful multilingual real estate websites. Continue reading to know how to build such successful websites.</p>\n<h2>The projects and authors</h2>\n<table class=\"table table-bordered\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image04.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790850\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-790850\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image04-300x209.png\" alt=\"image04\" width=\"300\" height=\"209\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image04-300x209.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image04-768x535.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image04-1024x714.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image04.png 1241w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></td>\n<td><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"http://antonini-realty.com/\">antonini-realty.com</a><br />\n<strong>Location</strong>: Umbria, Italy<br />\n<strong>Languages</strong>: Italian, English, Dutch<br />\n<strong>Properties</strong>: Mainly historical buildings<br />\n<strong>Number of properties:</strong> 200+<br />\n<strong>WordPress theme</strong>: Real Homes<br />\n<strong>Number of people working on the project:</strong> 2</p>\n<table width=\"320\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding-bottom: 30px;\" width=\"67\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-790865\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image02-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"image02\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image02-150x150.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image02-90x90.jpg 90w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image02.jpg 210w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px\" /></td>\n<td width=\"253\"><strong>Interviewee: </strong>Caroline van Agteren, a real-estate agent and the website co-owner</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790867\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-790867\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08-300x218.png\" alt=\"image08\" width=\"300\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08-150x109.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08-300x218.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08-768x559.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08-1024x745.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image08.png 1215w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></td>\n<td><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"http://mcgillimmobilier.com\">mcgillimmobilier.com</a><br />\n<strong>Location</strong>: Montreal, Canada<br />\n<strong>Languages</strong>: French, English<br />\n<strong>Properties: </strong>Condos<br />\n<strong>Number of properties</strong>: 5000+<br />\n<strong>WordPress theme</strong>: A theme built from scratch<br />\n<strong>People working on the project</strong>: 4</p>\n<table width=\"320\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding-bottom: 30px;\" width=\"71\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-790881\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image18.jpg\" alt=\"image18\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image18-90x90.jpg 90w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image18.jpg 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px\" /></td>\n<td width=\"249\"><strong>Interviewee: </strong>Ildar Khakimov, WordPress developer from <a href=\"http://qc-digital.com/\">qc-digital.com</a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790885\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-790885\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09-300x294.jpg\" alt=\"image09\" width=\"300\" height=\"294\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09-150x147.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09-300x294.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09-768x754.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09-1024x1005.jpg 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image09.jpg 1391w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></td>\n<td><strong>Website</strong>: <a href=\"http://imoalk.com/\">imoalk.com</a><br />\n<strong>Location:</strong> Portugal<br />\n<strong>Languages:</strong> Portuguese, English, French<br />\n<strong>Properties: </strong>Houses along the coast<br />\n<strong>Number of properties:</strong> 400+<br />\n<strong>WordPress theme:</strong> A Toolset theme<br />\n<strong>People working on the project:</strong> 1</p>\n<table width=\"320\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"70\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-790886\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image06-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"image06\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image06-150x150.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image06-300x300.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image06-90x90.jpg 90w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image06.jpg 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px\" /></td>\n<td width=\"250\"><strong>Interviewee</strong>: Antonio Almeida, a marketer who knows how to put things together with WordPress.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Rule number one: Develop customer interest</h2>\n<p>Before you get your hands dirty implementing a real estate website you need to <strong>understand the site’s purpose</strong>. Don’t for a minute think that building a real estate website comes down to putting properties on display and providing a good search.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image15.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-790895 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image15-300x204.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"204\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image15-150x102.jpg 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image15-300x204.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image15-768x521.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image15.jpg 900w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><strong>Did you ever experience something like this?</strong> You are looking for an apartment to buy, you find a great looking picture of the place you need. The price looks promising too. You contact the agency and you hear: “We are sorry but this property has been already sold/booked. However, we have a similar one available that might interest you”.</p>\n<p>The goal of a real estate site is to generate leads. Lead generation is the <strong>initiation of consumer interest</strong> or inquiry into products or services your business offers. If you want to build a successful real estate website, you need to provide stuff that will pique a customer’s interest. Interest in the site itself or in a specific offer, this would be the first step. The next one is to encourage the customer to take the desired action.</p>\n<p>What are these actions? Let’s find out from our interviewees.</p>\n<h2>Rule number two: Get the best pictures you can</h2>\n<p>Attractive pictures won’t be your secret weapon. In the real estate business, it’s a necessity<strong>.</strong> The competition in the market is huge. If you don’t impress your visitors in a few seconds they will leave your site and go to your competitors.</p>\n<p><strong>Caroline van Agteren,</strong> a real estate agent from Antonini Really agency in Italy, confirms that. When asked what is a must-have for a real estate site to be successful, she explains:</p>\n<blockquote><p>“Pictures! Now everything is very visual. We get compliments on our photo work. In the end, the looks determine whether someone falls in love with a property.”</p></blockquote>\n<p>Indeed, the pictures on Caroline’s site are beautiful:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image13.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790901\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-790901\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image13-300x224.png\" alt=\"image13\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image13-150x112.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image13-300x224.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image13-768x573.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image13.png 956w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><br />\nSource: <a href=\"http://antonini-realty.com/\">http://antonini-realty.com/</a> &#8211; Real Estate broker in Italy, Umbria</td>\n<td><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image11.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790902\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-790902\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image11-300x198.png\" alt=\"image11\" width=\"300\" height=\"198\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image11-150x99.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image11-300x198.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image11-768x506.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image11.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>If a property doesn’t meet specific criteria, it won’t be accepted.</p>\n<blockquote><p>“They have to be nice, charming, appealing, but can be a total ruin, .”</p></blockquote>\n<p>says Caroline.</p>\n<h3>Featuring the best properties</h3>\n<p>Although all three websites we present here are based on different WordPress themes, there is an interesting “coincidence” in their homepage layout.</p>\n<p>First of all, each of the three sites has a big slider in the “above the fold” section.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"33%\">\n<p><div id=\"attachment_790916\" style=\"width: 239px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image05.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790916\"><img class=\"wp-image-790916\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image05-300x212.png\" alt=\"image05\" width=\"229\" height=\"162\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image05-150x106.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image05-300x212.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image05-768x542.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image05.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 229px) 100vw, 229px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Slider with properties on imoalk.com</p></div></td>\n<td width=\"33%\">\n<p><div id=\"attachment_790924\" style=\"width: 240px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image01.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790924\"><img class=\"wp-image-790924\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image01-300x205.png\" alt=\"Slider with properties on mcgillimmobilier.com\" width=\"230\" height=\"157\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image01-300x205.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image01-768x524.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image01.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 230px) 100vw, 230px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Slider with properties on mcgillimmobilier.com</p></div></td>\n<td width=\"33%\">\n<p><div id=\"attachment_790930\" style=\"width: 239px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image21.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790930\"><img class=\"wp-image-790930\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image21-300x195.png\" alt=\"Slider with properties on antonini-realty.com\" width=\"229\" height=\"149\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image21-300x195.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image21-768x499.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image21.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 229px) 100vw, 229px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Slider with properties on antonini-realty.com</p></div></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The best pictures have been put in sliders to impress the visitors and keep them on the site.</p>\n<p>Slightly below the slider, there comes a showcase of featured properties. Again, each of the websites includes such a showcase. Another “coincidence”? No way.</p>\n<p>Our second interview <strong>Ildar Khakimov </strong>from Canada, co-author of the <a href=\"http://www.mcgillimmobilier.com/\">mcgillimmobilier.com</a>, comments: “Our homepage is a showcase of our best properties. We present our best offerings with big beautiful pictures and just enough text to entice the visitor to click to learn more”. Here’s an example:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_790964\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image03.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790964\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-790964\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image03-300x259.png\" alt=\"Showcase of condos at mcgillimmobilier.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"259\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image03-300x259.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image03-768x663.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image03.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Showcase of condos at mcgillimmobilier.com</p></div>\n<p>“&#8230; entice the visitor to click more” &#8211; wisely summarized. In these words, Ildar also included the first <strong>call to action</strong> that has been planned for a prospect: to go to another page. This will be a single property page where there is much more space to present details.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Caroline adds “Accurate information is the key to selling. After a picture lures a client in, they need detailed information to understand what they are looking at.”</p></blockquote>\n<h2>Rule number three: Provide easy navigation leading to the contact person</h2>\n<p>No doubt accurate information about a property matters, but first your prospect needs to look up a property that suits them. To make this happen, you need to equip your site with a good search engine and navigation.</p>\n<blockquote><p>“Ease of navigation that allows visitors to find properties they&#8217;re interested in and <strong>clean design</strong> that doesn&#8217;t distract people<strong>” </strong>were the first two requirements Ildar listed when asked about the project must-haves.</p>\n<p>“We spent a lot of time around navigation and search, many versions were tried before we settled on the one that we&#8217;re using today.” says Ildar.</p></blockquote>\n<div id=\"attachment_790968\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image00.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790968\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-790968\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image00-300x218.png\" alt=\"Each single property page includes a contact information\" width=\"300\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image00-150x109.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image00-300x218.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image00-768x558.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image00.png 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Each single property page at <a href=\"http://www.mcgillimmobilier.com/\">http://www.mcgillimmobilier.com/</a> includes a contact information</p></div>\n<p>However, at the end of the day, your business goal is to make the prospect <strong>contact the agency</strong>. Here’s space for including another call to action.</p>\n<p>No wonder that <strong>all three sites have another thing in common</strong>: each single-property page ends with contact information encouraging the visitor to contact the agency.</p>\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n<p>This requirement was also shortlisted on Ildar’s must-haves for the project:</p>\n<blockquote><p>“Comprehensive navigation, so a person can jump onto a specific agent&#8217;s page right from the property and see other properties sold by the same agent.”</p></blockquote>\n<p>Pick a random property on their site, scroll down the page and you will see contact information for the agent.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_790983\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image10.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790983\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-790983\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image10-300x231.png\" alt=\"Each property at http://www.antonini-realty.com includes a contact and agent information\" width=\"300\" height=\"231\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image10-300x231.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image10-768x590.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image10.png 942w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Each property at <a href=\"http://www.antonini-realty.com/\">http://www.antonini-realty.com/</a> includes a contact and agent information</p></div>\n<p>The same happens when you visit Caroline’s site.</p>\n<p>She explains: “Business and agent information are needed for those who are looking for assistance”. She adds that it also helps to create their own identity.</p>\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n<h3>Collect your contact data</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_791003\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image07.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-791003\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-791003\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image07-300x247.jpg\" alt=\"Each property of imoalk.com has an individual contact form\" width=\"300\" height=\"247\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image07-300x247.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image07-768x633.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image07-1024x844.jpg 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image07.jpg 1260w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Each property of imoalk.com has an individual contact form</p></div>\n<p>In his <a href=\"http://imoalk.com/\">imoalk.com</a> site, <strong>Antonio Almeida</strong> connected a contact form with a property.</p>\n<p>The contact form allows a visitor to contact the agency for details about <strong>this particular property </strong>and, in addition, <strong>collect</strong> and <strong>store</strong> the contact information together with the property in your WordPress database.</p>\n<p>So the agency not only receives the emails but can also access all collected contacts in the WordPress back-end. Being combined with properties it’s also a great source for statistics.</p>\n<p>The interesting part is that Antonio implemented this without using PHP, visit <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/2015/08/how-to-develop-a-multilingual-real-estate-site-with-wordpress-and-no-php#contact-form\">the case study</a> to see details.</p>\n<h2>Rule number four: Reach a wider audience</h2>\n<p>So you have nice pictures of properties, clean navigation, a good search, and smart calls to actions designed. Is this enough to succeed in the real estate business?</p>\n<p>Note that we described all the real estate site’s essentials with one silent assumption. The customer visited the site. But how can we be sure that there will be any visitors? <strong>All the carefully designed facilities are worth nothing if only few people visit your website.</strong></p>\n<p>Your next goal is to make the website attract traffic.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image20.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-791024 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image20-290x300.jpg\" alt=\"Global Languages Translate Concept\" width=\"290\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image20-145x150.jpg 145w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image20-290x300.jpg 290w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image20-768x795.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image20.jpg 869w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 290px) 100vw, 290px\" /></a>Providing good contents is always welcome. Search engines such as Google will appreciate that.</p>\n<p>The problem is that your competitors realize it too and will do the same. <strong>So you need to come up with something extra.</strong> Translating the site to foreign languages seemed to be a perfect option.</p>\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n<p>Caroline explains:</p>\n<blockquote><p>“We regard a multilingual site essential in this world. Clients no longer come to Italy and walk into your office to ask you whether you would like to sell them a house. They all hunt on the internet and mostly only contact you to organize the actual viewing. As there are many agencies out there we have to be pro-active and prepared.”</p></blockquote>\n<p>Now their site is available in three languages.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_791027\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-791027\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image17-300x171.png\" alt=\"Antonini Realty is available in three languages: Italian, English, and Dutch\" width=\"300\" height=\"171\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image17-300x171.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image17.png 328w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Antonini Realty is available in three languages: Italian, English, and Dutch</p></div>\n<blockquote style=\"display: table;\"><p>“Being in Italy, Italian is obvious, English is essential, Dutch since both I and one of my colleagues were born in Holland so our native language is Dutch. We would like to add more languages but are hesitant to do so without having a native speaker on board.”</p></blockquote>\n<p>“The amount of work to translate everything” was listed as one of the biggest challenges in Caroline’s project. She explains:</p>\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n<blockquote><p>“Certain words do not simply exist in another language or are hard to translate in one word, it takes the additional language as a whole to make it clear what it is all about.”</p></blockquote>\n<p>However,<strong> if something seems to be challenging for you there’s a good chance it will be tricky for your competitors as well</strong>. Why not use the difficulties as an opportunity to make your offer stand out?</p>\n<p>Providing the contents in different languages has paid off. The Antonini Reality site attracted customers from Australia, Sweden, the US, and Belgium. “They really are from all over the place,” says Caroline.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_791205\" style=\"width: 286px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-791205\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image12.png\" alt=\"impalk.com is available in three languages: Portuguese, English, and French\" width=\"276\" height=\"146\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">impalk.com is available in three languages: Portuguese, English, and French</p></div>\n<p>Presenting his site in <strong>three different languages</strong> was an obvious decision for Antonio. He used WPML on a number of different sites he built. <a href=\"http://imoalk.com/\">imoalk.com</a> is available in Portuguese, French, and English.</p>\n<p>Ildar’s site was no exception. Currently, his site is available in two languages <strong>French and English</strong> and they plan to add more:</p>\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n<blockquote><p>“We&#8217;re in a French-speaking province Quebec which is part of the English-speaking Canada. Most definitely, we would be missing out on a large part of the market if we didn&#8217;t translate the site in English, we&#8217;re also working on more languages.”</p></blockquote>\n<p>All our interviewees find working with WPML easy and they translated all the site’s elements into different languages. If you need some technical details, visit Antonio&#8217;s <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/2015/08/how-to-develop-a-multilingual-real-estate-site-with-wordpress-and-no-php/#multilingual\">case study.</a></p>\n<h2>Rule number five: Get ready for challenges, it’s normal</h2>\n<p>Challenges in the process of building a real estate website are inevitable. They will vary depending on the size of your project, the tools and resources you have, including people involved, their skills, and experience.</p>\n<p><strong>The good news is that the solutions to overcome the obstacles are out there.</strong> Here are some problems our interviewees faced.</p>\n<h3>Finding a good web designer</h3>\n<p>For Caroline, the biggest challenge in the project was to find a good web designer. By “web designer” she has a WordPress techie in mind, not a graphic designer. Eventually, the theme they used was a ready-to-use stock theme dedicated to a real estate website. They picked it because of its look and aimed at adjusting it to their needs.</p>\n<p>They needed a WordPress expert to get started with on the technical part, including the WPML setup.</p>\n<blockquote><p>“After a while when the basics were done, I had spent some time with him to solve various problems. It did not seem too complicated and I basically took over…”</p></blockquote>\n<p>Caroline comments. She proves that when you really want to you can overcome the obstacles you may face:</p>\n<blockquote><p>“&#8230; It took some trial and error but by now I know how to do all we need. I have no previous experience but am an entrepreneur and will do anything if needed for my company, within bounds of it being realistic and not a total waste of time.”</p></blockquote>\n<div id=\"attachment_791243\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image14.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-791243 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image14-300x203.jpg\" alt=\"If you need a unique design for your real estate website hire a graphic designer\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image14-300x203.jpg 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image14-768x520.jpg 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image14.jpg 900w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">If you need a unique design for your real estate website hire a graphic designer</p></div>\n<p>Finding a good web designer was important for Ildar too. They needed a typical graphic designer tough. They, as WordPress developers, could manage everything else. To find a great web designer they announced a sort of competition and picked the best one:</p>\n<blockquote style=\"display: table;\"><p>“We had several submissions then went with the designer we liked the most and that designer built out the rest of the pages”</p></blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Custom search engine</h3>\n<div id=\"attachment_791212\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image16.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-791212 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image16-300x181.png\" alt=\"Search engine on www.mcgillimmobilier.com built by Ildar’s team\" width=\"300\" height=\"181\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image16-300x181.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image16-768x464.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image16-1024x618.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image16.png 1186w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Search engine on <a href=\"http://www.mcgillimmobilier.com\">www.mcgillimmobilier.com</a> built by Ildar’s team</p></div>\n<p>The biggest challenge Ildar’s team was facing was building a good search engine. Ildar’s site includes more than 5000+ properties.</p>\n<blockquote style=\"display: table;\"><p>“Every 4th new condo is sold through McGill Immobilier,” says Ildar, so implementing a flexible search engine wasn’t a trivial thing. They wanted to “ensure that the visitors were 100% satisfied with the experience” so it took them several trials to determine the best one.</p></blockquote>\n<div id=\"attachment_791234\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image19.png\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-791234\"><img class=\"wp-image-791234 size-medium\" src=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image19-300x239.png\" alt=\"Search engine on imoalk.com built by Antonio without PHP coding\" width=\"300\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image19-300x239.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image19-768x613.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/image19.png 988w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Search engine on imoalk.com built by Antonio without PHP coding</p></div>\n<p>Surprisingly, building the search prototype turned out to be a piece of cake for Antonio. He used the Views plugin to handle it. The Views plugin he used is famous for its support of the <a href=\"https://wp-types.com/documentation/user-guides/front-page-filters/\">Parametric Search</a> feature that lets you create a powerful parametric search without using PHP.</p>\n<div class=\"clear\"></div>\n<h2>Final thoughts</h2>\n<p>It doesn’t matter if you build a real estate site or any other WordPress based site. At the end of the day, there will always be something you would like to do differently and better.</p>\n<p>Ildar’s team tried many versions for their search before they settled on the one they use today. When closing the interview, Antonio was still working on some enhancements. Caroline admits that it’s pretty likely that their site will look slightly different in another 6 weeks:</p>\n<blockquote><p>“We like to criticize ourselves in every possible way to be ahead of others doing so, so we are not often completely satisfied. Even right now we would like to add this, remove that, change this, etc..”</p></blockquote>\n<p><strong>Nevertheless, all our interviewees were so proud of their projects</strong> that they decided to submit them to our WPML showcase. And most importantly, they can see other opportunities in having a nice multilingual website. Caroline summarizes:</p>\n<blockquote><p>“Working with WPML and multilingual sites is good for our own development, for our image, our employees, and business. It does motivate our team a lot to have an international approach and image, and a happy team is good for business. They need the right tools to work with and a WPML supported site is one of them.</p>\n<p>I don’t know how anything could function without it to be honest. That would really mean going back to the dark ages…”</p></blockquote>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=E7E9z2HGOpU:GaI1RKbCAm4:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=E7E9z2HGOpU:GaI1RKbCAm4:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=E7E9z2HGOpU:GaI1RKbCAm4:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=E7E9z2HGOpU:GaI1RKbCAm4:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=E7E9z2HGOpU:GaI1RKbCAm4:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=E7E9z2HGOpU:GaI1RKbCAm4:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/E7E9z2HGOpU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/five-rules-you-should-know-before-building-wordpress-real-estate-sites/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/five-rules-you-should-know-before-building-wordpress-real-estate-sites/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:119:\"WooCommerce Compatibility – Prices by User Roles, Woo Convert to Customer, YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp, RedSys GateWay\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/-PBh9snIzX0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wpml.org/2016/01/woocommerce-compatibility/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 21 Jan 2016 16:04:12 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Compatibility\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"https://wpml.org/?p=793411\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:355:\"WooCommerce Multilingual is a very important project for us, today we are happy to announce that we have 4 WooCommerce Extensions to add to our compatibility list. The extensions are Prices by User Roles, Woo Convert to Customer, YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp, RedSys Gateway for WooCommerce If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Amit\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5006:\"<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce-multilingual/\" title=\"WooCommerce Multilingual\" target=\"_blank\">WooCommerce Multilingual</a> is a very important project for us, today we are happy to announce that we have 4 WooCommerce Extensions to add to our compatibility list. </p>\n<p>The extensions are <a title=\"Prices by User Roles\" href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/woocommerce-prices-by-user-role/8562616\">Prices by User Roles</a>, <a title=\"Woo Convert to Customer\" href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/woo-convert-to-customer/12698348/\">Woo Convert to Customer</a>, <a title=\"YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp\" href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/\">YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp</a>, <a title=\"RedSys Gateway for WooCommerce\" href=\"http://codection.com/producto/redsys-gateway-for-woocommerce/\">RedSys Gateway for WooCommerce</a></p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Multilingual Ready Themes \" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/\">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Multilingual Ready Plugins \" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/\">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you&#8217;re a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/\">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our <a title=\"Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins\" href=\"https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/\">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin <strong>Multilingual Ready</strong>.</p>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Prices by Users Roles</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/woocommerce-prices-by-user-role/8562616\"></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>WooCommerce Prices By User Role is the WordPress plugin which extends the popular e-commerce plugin WooCommerce to add role based pricing to default functionality.</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/woocommerce-prices-by-user-role/8562616\">Purchase Prices by Users Roles</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">Woo Convert to Customer</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/woo-convert-to-customer/12698348\"></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>WooConvert to Customers help any shop owner convert more customers by providing automatically discount on products that visitors are interested in.</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/woo-convert-to-customer/12698348\" target=\"_blank\">Purchase Convert to Customer</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/\"></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Make specific marketing campaigns via email for customers of your shop by using MailChimp. If you can manage your contacts in a more systematic way, you can surely be more convincing and you’ll see sales in your shop increase.</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/\">Purchase YITH WooCommerce Mailchimp</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feature\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">RedSys Gateway for WooCommerce</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://codection.com/producto/redsys-gateway-for-woocommerce/\"></a></p>\n<blockquote><p>Conecta tu pasarela de pago RedSys a tu tienda online WooCommerce.</p></blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a class=\"button download-button vt-p\" href=\"http://codection.com/producto/redsys-gateway-for-woocommerce/\">Purchase RedSys Gateway for WooCommerce</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=-PBh9snIzX0:NMriXK9YDCA:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=-PBh9snIzX0:NMriXK9YDCA:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=-PBh9snIzX0:NMriXK9YDCA:gIN9vFwOqvQ\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=-PBh9snIzX0:NMriXK9YDCA:gIN9vFwOqvQ\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=-PBh9snIzX0:NMriXK9YDCA:V_sGLiPBpWU\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=-PBh9snIzX0:NMriXK9YDCA:V_sGLiPBpWU\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/-PBh9snIzX0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"